                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">717.2114/74: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-20T11:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>349. My telegram of September 19, 2 p.m. Since the newspapers here are stating
                    that the United States desired an adjustment of the San Andres question because
                    we wished to acquire the island[s] from Colombia and it is even being intimated
                    that a portion of the purchase price will be paid secretly to Conservative
                    officials here, I recommend that I be authorized not only to furnish the press
                    with a copy of the Department’s statement about the negotiations but also to
                    state orally at the same time that the United States has no intention of
                    acquiring the islands for itself.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
